Tammy Petersen, News24A filling station owner and seven others were arrested when drugs worth R100 000 were found at a Gugulethu garage. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A petrol filling station owner and seven others were arrested on Saturday when approximately 2 000 units of drugs were found in a storeroom at a Gugulethu garage, Western Cape police have confirmed.Police searched the filling station in NY1 after a tip-off about drug-related activities, spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Andre Traut said."Hidden in a storeroom, members came across a large quantity of mandrax tablets with an estimated street value to the tune of R100 000," he said.A substantial amount of cash was also confiscated.The business owner, a 47-year-old woman, and seven men aged between 23 and 57 were arrested and are expected in the Philippi Magistrate's Court on Monday.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.